<DOC><DOCNO> AP880708-0005 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-08-88 0111EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Burma-Releases     07-08 0160</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Burma-Releases,0165</SECOND><HEAD>Authorities Free 390 People Arrested In Riots</HEAD><DATELINE>RANGOON, Burma (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Authorities have released 390 peoplearrested in student riots in March and June, the state radio said.   The broadcast said those freed Thursday included 229 students,147 civilians and 14 government employees. It said 240 people werefreed in the national capital of Rangoon and the others in thecities of Pegu, Prome and Moulmein.   The broadcast said some people were freed unconditionally andothers on bail. It did not say how many people had been arrested,but it said releases will continue.   In the most recent riots in Rangoon on June 21, universitystudents demanded that the government legalize student unions andfree students detained in earlier protests.   Authorities said nine people were killed when thousands ofdemonstrators clashed with riot police. Seventy-seven people werearrested in connection with that riot, they said.   Authorities closed most educational institutions and imposed acurfew until Aug. 17.</TEXT></DOC>